> Fresh, flavorful, and fast: that's how we get you summer-ready! We send fresh ingredients (to help you meet your summer goals), for flavorful recipes that get you out of the kitchen fast. This little 10-minute number features fully cooked pulled pork you'll combine with BBQ seasoning, BBQ sauce, and hearty black beans. Scoop into warm tortillas and top with a refreshing pineapple-lime salsa, then garnish with a fresh squeeze of lime and a sprinkle of cilantro and hot sauce (if you like!).

Drain and rinse @black beans{1%unit}.

Place @pulled pork{8%ounce} in a large #microwave-safe bowl{}; shred into
bite-size pieces using your hands or 2 forks. Add @BBQ sauce{4%tablespoon},
@sweet and smoky BBQ seasoning{1%tablespoon}, half the beans (all for 4
servings), @salt{}, and @pepper{}; mix to combine. Cover #bowl{} with
#plastic wrap{}; microwave until warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, wash and dry produce.

Drain @pineapple{4%ounce}. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Quarter
@lime{1%unit}.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6%unit} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until
warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

In a small bowl, combine pineapple, half the cilantro, and juice from one
lime wedge (juice from two lime wedges for 4 servings); season with pepper
to taste.

Divide tortillas between plates and fill with pork and beans. Top tacos
with pineapple salsa. Sprinkle with remaining cilantro and drizzle with
as much @hot sauce{1%teaspoon} as you like. Serve with remaining lime wedges.